==Results== ===2005=== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Sacrifice (2005) |image=Tnasacrifice2005.jpg |tagline="Pain" |caption=Promotional poster featuring [[Scott Levy|Raven]] |promotion=[[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling]] |date=August 14, 2005 |attendance=775<ref name="PWHSac05">{{cite web|url=http://www.prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/usa/misc/tna/sacrifice.html#2005|title=Sacrifice 2005 at Pro Wrestling History.com|accessdate=2008-11-02|publisher=Pro Wrestling History.com}}</ref> |venue=[[TNA Impact! Zone]] |city=[[Orlando, Florida]] |lastevent=[[TNA No Surrender#2005|No Surrender (2005)]] |nextevent=[[TNA Unbreakable|Unbreakable]] |event=Sacrifice |nextevent2=[[TNA Sacrifice#2006|Sacrifice (2006)]] |lastevent2='''''First''''' }}
'''Sacrifice (2005)''' was a [[professional wrestling]] [[pay-per-view]] (PPV) [[List of TNA pay-per-view events|event]] produced by [[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling]] (TNA), which took place on August 14, 2005 at the [[TNA Impact! Zone]] in [[Orlando, Florida]]. It was the first event under the Sacrifice chronology. Nine [[Mock combat|professional wrestling matches]] were featured on the event's [[Card (sports)|card]].
*Pre-Show Match: [[GermÃ¡n Figueroa|Apolo]] and [[Sonny Siaki]] defeated [[Mikey Batts]] and [[Vincent Clark|Jerrelle Clark]] (04:25) **Siaki pinned Batts after a [[Professional wrestling throws#Gorilla press slam|Gorilla press slam]]/[[Cutter (professional wrestling)|Cutter]] combination. *[[Chris Sabin]], [[Sonjay Dutt]] and [[Shark Boy]] defeated [[The Diamonds in the Rough]] ([[Pat Kenney|Simon Diamond]], [[David Young (wrestler)|David Young]] and [[Elix Skipper]]) (07:24) **Sabin pinned Skipper with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)#Small package|Small Package]]. *[[Alex Shelley]] defeated [[JosÃ© Luis Jair Soria|Shocker]] (08:55) **Shelley pinned Shocker with his feet on the ropes. *[[Chris Parks|Abyss]] (with [[James Mitchell (manager)|James Mitchell]]) defeated [[Lance Hoyt]] (09:12) **Abyss pinned Hoyt after a [[Powerslam#Spinning side slam|Black Hole Slam]]. *[[3Live Kru]] ([[Ron Killings]] and [[Konnan]]) defeated [[Monty Sopp|Kip James]] and [[Monty Brown]] (with [[Brian Gerard James|B.G. James]] as [[Referee (professional wrestling)#Special referees|Special Guest Referee]]) (07:31) **Konnan pinned Kip after a [[Facebuster#Sitout facebuster|Facejam]] after B.G. James intercepted Kip's chair and attacked him. *[[Christopher Daniels]] defeated [[Austin Aries]] (09:30) **Daniels pinned Aries after the [[Facebuster#Lifting double underhook facebuster|Angel's Wings]]. **Aries was selected in an internet poll over [[Roderick Strong]], [[Jay Lethal]] and [[Evan Bourne|Matt Sydal]]. *[[Jerry Lynn]] defeated [[Sean Waltman]] (15:23) **Lynn pinned Waltman with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)#Victory roll|Victory Roll]]. **After the match, an irate Waltman attacked Lynn until Shark Boy, Chris Sabin, and Sonjay Dutt came out to help Lynn. *[[Team Canada (TNA)|Team Canada]] ([[Petey Williams]], [[Robert Roode|Bobby Roode]], [[Eric Young (wrestler)|Eric Young]] and [[Alastair Ralphs|A-1]]) (with [[Scott D'Amore|Coach D'Amore]]) defeated [[America's Most Wanted (professional wrestling)|America's Most Wanted]] ([[Chris Harris (wrestler)|Chris Harris]] and [[James Storm]]) and [[The Naturals]] ([[Chase Stevens]] and [[Andy Douglas]]) (with [[Jimmy Hart]]) in an [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Multiple man teamed matches|Eight Man Tag Team match]] (11:10) **Roode pinned Stevens with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)#Small package|Small Package]]. *[[Samoa Joe]] defeated [[A.J. Styles]] to win the [[TNA 2005 Super X Cup Tournament|2005 Super X Cup Tournament]] (15:05) **Joe forced Styles to submit with the [[Professional wrestling holds#Rear naked choke|Coquina Clutch]] to earn a shot at the [[TNA X Division Championship]]. *[[Jeff Jarrett]] and [[Terry Gerin|Rhino]] defeated [[Scott Levy|Raven]] and [[Terry Brunk|Sabu]] (13:09) **Rhino pinned Raven after a [[Professional wrestling attacks#Spear|Gore]] through a [[Table (furniture)|table]] set up in the corner. {{-}}
===2006=== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Sacrifice (2006) |image=Tnasacrifice2006.jpg |tagline=Global Turmoil |promotion=[[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling]] |date=May 14, 2006 |attendance=900 |venue=[[TNA Impact! Zone]] |city=[[Orlando, Florida]] |lastevent=[[Lockdown (2006)]] |nextevent=[[Slammiversary (2006)]] |event=Sacrifice |nextevent2=[[TNA Sacrifice#2007|Sacrifice (2007)]] |lastevent2=[[TNA Sacrifice#2005|Sacrifice (2005)]] }}
'''Sacrifice (2006)''' was a [[professional wrestling]] [[pay-per-view]] (PPV) [[List of TNA pay-per-view events|event]] produced by [[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling]] (TNA), which took place on May 14, 2006 at the [[TNA Impact! Zone]] in [[Orlando, Florida]]. It was the second event under the Sacrifice chronology. Eight [[Mock combat|professional wrestling matches]] were featured on the event's [[Card (sports)|card]].
*[[Jushin Liger]] (with [[Rocky Romero|Black Tiger IV]], [[Minoru Tanaka (wrestler)|Minoru Tanaka]], and [[Hirooki Goto]]) defeated [[Petey Williams]] (with [[Eric Young (wrestler)|Eric Young]], [[Johnny Devine]], and [[Tyson Dux]]) in a [[TNA 2006 World X Cup Tournament|World X Cup match]] (07:16) **Liger pinned Williams after a [[Facebuster#Feint backdrop wheelbarrow facebuster|CTB]]. *[[America's Most Wanted (professional wrestling)|America's Most Wanted]] ([[Chris Harris (wrestler)|Chris Harris]] and [[James Storm]]) defeated [[A.J. Styles and Christopher Daniels]] to retain the [[NWA World Tag Team Championship]] (15:30) **Harris pinned Styles after hitting him with a [[Baton (law enforcement)|nightstick]] thrown down from the rafters by [[Gail Kim]]. *[[Scott Levy|Raven]] defeated [[Alastair Ralphs|A-1]] (with [[Larry Zbyszko]]) (05:19) **Raven pinned A-1 after a [[DDT (professional wrestling)#Snap DDT|Raven Effect DDT]]. *[[Robert Roode|Bobby Roode]] (with [[Scott D'Amore|Coach D'Amore]]) defeated [[Terry Gerin|Rhino]] (12:07) **Roode pinned Rhino after a [[Professional wrestling attacks#Lariat|Northern Lariat]]. *[[New Age Outlaws|The James Gang]] ([[Brian Gerard James|B.G. James]] and [[Monty Sopp|Kip James]]) defeated [[Dudley Boyz|Team 3D]] ([[Mark LoMonaco|Brother Ray]] and [[Devon Hughes|Brother Devon]]) (09:35) **B.G. pinned Devon after hitting him with a lead pipe. *[[Petey Williams]] won a [[TNA 2006 World X Cup Tournament|World X Cup Gauntlet]] (19:21) **Also in the match: Minoru Tanaka, [[T.J. Perkins|Puma]], [[Chris Sabin]], Hirooki Goto, [[Incognito (wrestler)|Incognito]], Johnny Devine, [[Sonjay Dutt]], Black Tiger IV, Magno, Eric Young, [[Alex Shelley]], Jushin Liger, [[JosÃ© Luis Jair Soria|Shocker]], Tyson Dux, and [[Jay Lethal]]. **Williams pinned Puma after a [[Piledriver (professional wrestling)#Flip piledriver|Canadian Destroyer]]. **After the match, [[Kevin Nash]] entered the ring and delivered a [[Powerbomb#Release powerbomb|Jackknife Powerbomb]] to Puma. *[[Steve Borden|Sting]] and [[Samoa Joe]] defeated [[Jeff Jarrett]] and [[Scott Steiner]] (with [[Gail Kim]]) (14:24) **Joe pinned Jarrett after a [[Professional wrestling throws#Muscle buster|Muscle Buster]]. **After the match, Steiner and Jarrett attacked Sting until [[New Age Outlaws|The James Gang]], [[Terry Gerin|Rhino]], and [[Christopher Daniels]] (among others) came out to help Sting. *[[Jason Reso|Christian Cage]] defeated [[Chris Parks|Abyss]] (with [[James Mitchell (manager)|James Mitchell]]) in a [[Tables, Ladders, and Chairs match#Total Nonstop Action Wrestling|Full Metal Mayhem match]] to retain the [[NWA World Heavyweight Championship]] (26:01) **Cage grabbed the belt to win the match and reclaim the physical title belt, which had been stolen by Abyss at [[Lockdown (2006)|Lockdown]]. {{-}}
===2007=== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Sacrifice (2007) |image=Tnasacrifice2007.jpg |caption=Promotional poster featuring [[Scott Steiner]], [[Travis Tomko|Tomko]], and [[Jason Reso|Christian Cage]] |tagline="Give Nothing... but Take All" |promotion=[[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling]] |date=May 13, 2007 |attendance=900 |venue=[[TNA Impact! Zone]] |city=[[Orlando, Florida]] |lastevent=[[Lockdown (2007)]] |nextevent=[[Slammiversary (2007)]] |event=Sacrifice |nextevent2=[[Sacrifice (2008)]] |lastevent2=[[TNA Sacrifice#2006|Sacrifice (2006)]] }} '''Sacrifice (2007)''' was a [[professional wrestling]] [[pay-per-view]] [[List of TNA pay-per-view events|event]] produced by [[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling]] (TNA), which took place on May 13, 2007 at the [[TNA Impact! Zone]] in [[Orlando, Florida]]. It was the third event under the Sacrifice chronology. Nine [[Mock combat|professional wrestling matches]] were featured on the event's [[Card (sports)|card]].
*[[Chris Sabin]] defeated [[Jay Lethal]] and [[Sonjay Dutt]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|Three Way match]] to retain the [[TNA X Division Championship]] (13:00) **Sabin pinned Dutt with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)#Roll-up|roll-up]]. **After the match, Dutt attacked [[Kevin Nash]]. *[[Robert Roode]] (with [[Tracy Brookshaw|Ms. Brooks]]) defeated [[Jeff Jarrett]] (11:21) **Roode pinned Jarrett with [[Suplex#Fisherman suplex|the Payoff]]. *[[Christopher Daniels]] defeated [[Terry Gerin|Rhino]] (10:01) **Daniels pinned Rhino after hitting him with a [[baseball bat]]. *[[Basham Brothers|Basham and Damaja]] (with [[Christy Hemme]]) defeated [[Monty Sopp|Kip James]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Handicap match|Handicap match]] (04:26) **Basham pinned James after a [[Professional wrestling aerial techniques#Diving headbutt|diving headbutt]]. **[[Brian Gerard James|B.G. James]] was scheduled for the match, but was attacked by Basham and Damaja beforehand. *[[Chris Harris (wrestler)|Chris Harris]] defeated [[James Storm]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Texas Death match|Texas Death match]] (17:14) **Harris won the match when he pinned Storm after hitting him with a beer bottle and Storm could not answer the 10 count. *[[Jerry Lynn]] defeated [[Tiger Mask IV]], [[Alex Shelley]], and [[Brandon Silvestry|Senshi]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|Four-Corners match]] (10:43) **Lynn pinned Shelley with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)#Roll-up|roll-up]]. **After the match, Shelley and [[Chris Sabin]] attacked Lynn until [[Bob Backlund]] made the save. *[[Dudley Boyz|Team 3D]] ([[Mark LoMonaco|Brother Ray]] and [[Devon Hughes|Brother Devon]]) defeated [[Scott Steiner]] and [[Travis Tomko|Tomko]] and [[The Latin American Xchange]] ([[Nelson Erazo|Homicide]] and [[Shawn Hernandez|Hernandez]]) in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|Three-Way Dance]] to retain the [[TNA World Tag Team Championship|World Tag Team Championship]] (12:38) **Ray pinned Tomko after a [[Professional wrestling double-team maneuvers#Death Drop|3D]] **After the match, Tomko attacked Steiner but he was saved by his brother [[Rick Steiner]] *[[Samoa Joe]] defeated [[A.J. Styles]] (12:48) **Joe pinned Styles after a [[Suplex#Sleeper suplex|rear naked choke suplex]]. *[[Kurt Angle]] defeated [[Steve Borden|Sting]] and [[Jason Reso|Christian Cage]] (c) in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|Three Way match]] to win the [[TNA World Heavyweight Championship|World Heavyweight Championship]] (10:45) **Angle forced Sting to submit with the [[Professional wrestling holds#Ankle lock|Ankle Lock]] while he had Cage pinned. The referee [[Dusty Finish|declared]] Angle the winner. **The NWA severed all business relationships with TNA earlier in the day, regaining control of the [[NWA World Heavyweight Championship]] and [[NWA World Tag Team Championship]], stripping Cage and Team 3D of the titles before the event.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://one.revver.com/watch/267425/flv/affiliate/87879|title=NWA/Trobich strips TNA/Cage/Team 3-D of NWA branded Championships |accessdate=2007-07-19|date=2007-05-13}}</ref> **Angle's victory was later revoked as the final decision resulted in the new title being vacated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prowrestling.com/article/results/1108|title=TNA iMPACT Results - May 17, 2007|date=2007-05-17|accessdate=2007-11-13|author=Larry Csonka|publisher=ProWrestling.com}}</ref>
